Please note that this function considers 1 as not a prime number, as it doesn't fit the traditional definition of a prime number (a prime number is a natural number greater than 1 that has no divisors other than 1 and itself). If you want to consider 1 as a prime number, you can modify the `isPrime` function accordingly.

