\section{Results}
\label{sec:results}

Some text in section 3.

\end{document}
```

In this example, the `\tableofcontents` command is placed where you want the TOC to appear in your document. The `\section`, `\subsection`, etc., commands are used to define the headings in your document. The `\label` command is used to assign a label to each section or subsection, which allows you to reference them in the TOC.

When you compile the document, the TOC will be generated automatically, showing the section and subsection titles and page numbers.

Output:

```
Table of Contents

1. Introduction ....................................................... 1
        1.1 Subsection 1 .................................................. 1
